# API Spector

This project uses API Spector for API testing. When editing collection files (`.spector`), environment files (`.env.json`), or generating test scripts, follow these references:

- `.cursor/docs/api-spector-scripting-reference.md` — Full `sp.*` scripting API
- `.cursor/docs/collection-file-format.md` — `.spector` and `.env.json` file structure
- `.cursor/docs/functional-testing-guide.md` — Functional test design patterns
- `.cursor/docs/security-testing-guide.md` — OWASP API Top 10 security tests

## Script conventions

- Wrap assertions in `sp.test('descriptive name', function() { ... })`
- Parse JSON once per script: `const json = sp.response.json();`
- Use `sp.environment.set("key", value)` to pass data between requests
- Use `{{variable}}` interpolation in URLs, headers, body, and scripts
- Hooks: `beforeAll` runs once per folder, `before` runs per request
